# Feature Request

### Relevant Package

@angular/core

### Description

The current syntax for structural directives is...awkward.

```ts
@Directive({ selector: 'myExample' })
export MyExampleDirective {
  @Input('myExampleA')
  a: number;

  @Input('myExampleB')
  b: number;

  @Input('myExampleC')
  c: number;
}
```

and then

```html
<div *myExample="let _; a: 1; b: 2; c: 3></div>
```

### Describe the solution you'd like

The initial `let _;` is not required.

```html
<div *myExample="a: 1; b: 2; c: 3></div>
```

### Describe alternatives you've considered

Typing `let _;`.

Combining everything into one params object.

I'm using a new Angular 12 project that was generated with the CLI with the defaults strict modes. 

Consider the following component: 

```ts

@Directive({
  selector: '[appFoo]'
})
export class FooDirective<T extends any[]> {
  @Input() appFoo!: T;
}
```

This will work as expected and infer the correct type for `T`:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/20522870/118646222-95e46100-b7e8-11eb-9fe7-11d949b546fb.png)


But if we change it to a custom type, it will infer it as `any`:

```ts
@Directive({
  selector: '[appFoo]'
})
export class FooDirective<T extends { id: number }> {
  @Input() appFoo!: T;
}
```

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/20522870/118646348-c3c9a580-b7e8-11eb-9327-7bc4466b9e26.png)

#### Feature Description


When adding multiple themes to one file... We are encouraged to only use the `<component>-color()` mixin. 

However, in order to do this we have to reference every single component in the library.... If we are using every component. 

Similar to the `mat.all-component-themes($my-theme);` can we get a `mat.all-component-colors($my-theme);`? 



